BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, April 28 (XINHUA)--The political group 
and economic groups of the Preliminary Working Committee (PWC) 
of the Preparatory Committee of the Special Administrative 
Region of Hong Kong will hold meetings respectively here next 
week. 
  The political group will meet from May 2 to 3 and the 
economic group from May 4 to 5. 
  Attending the meetings will be Lu Ping, deputy director and 
secretary general of the PWC and director of Hong Kong and Macao 
Affairs Office under the State Council, Zhou Nan, deputy 
director of the PWC and director of XINHUA NEWS AGENCY Hong Kong 
branch, as well as other related PWC members. 
  Those PWC members from the mainland will attend the ceremony 
to inaugurate the HK dollars issurance by Bank of China. 

